title: Advanced Interactivity
code: library(uwot) library(ggplot2) library(patchwork) library(ggiraph)   # Prepare Data & Colour Schemes penguins <- na.omit(read.csv(system.file("penguins.csv", package = "gg1d"))) palette_species <- c(Chinstrap = "#C55BCC", Adelie = "#FF7F02", Gentoo = "#047476")  # Create gg1d plot gg1d_penguins <- gg1d(   penguins,   col_id = "name",   interactive = FALSE,   col_sort = "species",   palettes = list(species = palette_species),   options = gg1d_options(relative_height_numeric = 1.2, show_legend = FALSE) )  # Perform the umap umap_mx <- umap(penguins, scale = "scale", n_neighbors = 70) df_umap <- as.data.frame(umap_mx) colnames(df_umap) <- c("UMAP_1", "UMAP_2") df_umap[["name"]] <- penguins[["name"]] df_umap[["species"]] <- penguins[["species"]]  # Create the umap plot gg_umap <- ggplot(df_umap, aes(x = UMAP_1, y = UMAP_2, colour = species, data_id = name)) +   geom_point_interactive() +   scale_color_manual(values = palette_species) +   theme_bw()  # Combine the gg1d plot and the umap using patchwork combined_plots <- free(gg_umap, type = "label") / free(gg1d_penguins, side = "tb")  # Make interactive interactive_multiplot <- girafe(ggobj = combined_plots, height_svg = 6, width_svg = 10, options)  # Add some settings to choose how to make combined plots interactive interactive_multiplot <- girafe_options(   x = interactive_multiplot,   opts_selection(type = "multiple", only_shiny = FALSE, css = "opacity: 1"),   opts_selection_inv(css = "opacity: 0.12") )  # Draw Interactive Multiplot interactive_multiplot

title: Gallery
text: simulated “Lazy Birdwatcher” dataset records magpie observations Robert Catherine. Robert doesn’t birdwatch weekends, resulting missing data days. pattern missingness, dependent person day, hard detect using one-dimensional EDA tools like skimr two-dimensional tools like ggpairs GGally package, don’t capture multi-variable interactions contributing missingness.
code: # Plot lazy birdwatcher dataset by Number of Magpies Observed gg1d(   lazy_birdwatcher,   col_sort = "Magpies",   palettes = list(     Birdwatcher = c(Robert = "#E69F00", Catherine = "#999999"),     Day = c(Weekday = "#999999", Weekend = "#009E73")   ),   options = gg1d_options(     show_legend = TRUE,     fontsize_barplot_y_numbers = 12,     legend_text_size = 16,     legend_key_size = 1,     legend_nrow = 1,   ) )

title: Parallel Coordinate Plots: Automaticaly Ordering Axes
text: Nearest Neighbour Tour (nn) path ‘next’ dimension always chosen based one lowest # crossings current current dimension Repetitive Nearest Neighbour Algorithm (rnn) Build separate nearest neighbour tour using dimension starting point. Return tour producing lowest number crossings Obviously certain configurations networks nearest neighbour algorithms find highly non-optimal paths. (partially) mitigate take best rnn solution improve using two-opt (.k.pairwise exchange) algorithm. Two-Opt systematically removes replaces two edges graph. run complete 2-opt local search, compare every possible valid combination swapping mechanism.

title: Parallel Coordinate Plots: Automaticaly Ordering Axes
text: can use algorithmic solution minimise metrics number crossings, including ‘approximations’ crossing numbers based subsets data (save time), mutual information distance pair dimensions (based Joe et al. 1989).

title: Visual Parameters for gg1d Plots — gg1d_options
text: colours_default Default colors categorical variables without custom palette. colours_default_logical Colors binary variables: vector three colors representing TRUE, FALSE, NA respectively (character). colours_missing Color missing (NA) values categorical plots (string). show_legend_titles Display titles legends (flag). legend_title_position Position legend title ("top", "bottom", "left", "right"). legend_nrow Number rows legend (number). legend_ncol Number columns legend. set, legend_nrow NULL (number). legend_title_size Size legend title text (number). legend_text_size Size text within legend (number). legend_key_size Size legend key symbols (number). legend_orientation_heatmap legend orientation "horizontal" "vertical". show_legend Display legend plot (flag). legend_position Position legend ("right", "left", "bottom", "top"). na_marker Text used mark NA values numeric plots (string). na_marker_size Size text marker NA values (number). na_marker_colour Color NA text marker (string). show_na_marker_categorical Show marker NA values categorical tiles (flag). show_na_marker_heatmap Show marker NA values heatmap tiles (flag). colours_heatmap_low Color lowest value heatmaps (string). colours_heatmap_high Color highest value heatmaps (string). transform_heatmap Transformation apply visualizing heatmap values ("identity", "log10", "log2"). fontsize_values_heatmap Font size heatmap values (number). show_values_heatmap Display numerical values heatmap tiles (flag). colours_values_heatmap Color heatmap values (string). vertical_spacing Space data row points (number). numeric_plot_type Type visualization numeric data: "bar" "heatmap". y_axis_position Position y-axis ("left" "right"). width controls much space present bars tiles within plot. Can 0-1 values 1 makes bars/tiles take 100% available space (gaps bars). relative_height_numeric many times taller numeric plots relative categorical tile plots. taken account numeric_plot_type == "bar" (number) cli_header Text used h1 header. Included can tweaked packages use gg1d, can customise info messages appear. interactive_svg_width, interactive_svg_height width height interactive graphic region (inches). used interactive = TRUE. fontsize_barplot_y_numbers fontsize text describing numeric barplot max & min values (number). max_digits_barplot_y_numbers Number digits round numeric barplot max min values (number). fontsize_y_title fontsize y axis titles (.k.data.frame column names) (number). beautify_text Beautify y-axis text legend titles capitalizing words adding spaces (flag).
